collections.name: Collection Nildes Carvalho Artworks and Connection
collections.description:
Nildes Carvalho da Silva is a Brazilian visual artist and writer with a background in Law, Philosophy, and Theology. Her work, which blends traditional and digital techniques, addresses themes such as solidarity, cultural identity, spirituality, and social justice. With a multidisciplinary approach, Nildes creates pieces that celebrate human diversity and promote deep dialogues on social and cultural realities. Her works are available on NFT marketplaces and in specialized galleries, ensuring authenticity and exclusivity. Nildes seeks to expand her presence in the global digital art market, connecting with collectors and international galleries. Her collection covers social, digital, portrait, identity, diversity, environmental, feminine, and contemporary art, offering a unique and reflective experience.

collections.name: Legends of the Rising Sun
collections.description:
Legends of the Rising Sun: A Samurai Odyssey
Step into a world of honor, valor, and timeless tradition with Legends of the Rising Sun, a meticulously crafted collection of 100 unique NFTs. This project celebrates the legendary samurai—warriors bound by the Bushido code, embodying virtues such as loyalty, courage, and mastery. Each piece in this collection is a visual and narrative masterpiece, blending intricate artistry with rich storytelling to immortalize these iconic figures.

From wandering ronin to noble daimyo, and from stealthy assassins to battle-hardened generals, each samurai tells their own story. The collection is divided into thematic categories, each capturing the essence of a different archetype:

Historical Legends: Honoring real and mythical figures whose legacies shaped the samurai ethos.
Armor Variations: Showcasing the beauty of ornate, battle-worn, and ceremonial armor styles.
Elemental Warriors: Samurai who channel the power of fire, water, wind, and more.

collections.name: Tristan und Isolde Poster Series
collections.description: The Tristan und Isolde Poster Series explores one of history’s most enduring love stories through the lens of modern art. This collection blends figurative and abstract styles, infusing the legend’s timeless themes of passion, heartbreak, and tragedy with bold Bauhaus geometry, muted tones, and golden hues. Each piece captures a moment, an emotion, or a memory from the tale, inviting viewers to reimagine the story of Tristan and Isolde in a contemporary, minimalist aesthetic.

collections.name: Yuan Dynasty Double-Fish-Handled Jar with Phoenix and Scrolling Peony Motifs
collections.description:
Era: Yuan Dynasty
Name: Double-Fish-Handled Jar with Phoenix and Scrolling Peony Motifs
Dimensions: Height: 36.4 cm, Mouth Diameter: 14.7 cm, Base Diameter: 16.3 cm

Characteristics:
	•	The jar features a small mouth and a flared rim.
	•	The shoulder and neck are adorned with double fish handles, positioned parallel to intricate phoenix motifs entwined with scrolling lotus patterns.
	•	Below the phoenix design, there are additional decorative elements, including miscellaneous treasure motifs.
	•	The same layer features inscriptions attributed to the “Strategies of Guiguzi.”
	•	The primary design theme of the jar is scrolling peony motifs.
	•	The jar has a plain base, wide foot, gracefully rounded shoulders, and a globular body that tapers below.
	•	The entire piece is painted using imported cobalt blue pigment (“Sumaliqing”).

Value:
This double-fish-handled jar is meticulously crafted with a well-proportioned form and exquisite workmanship. The phoenix designs are vivid and lifelike,

collections.name: Project Solara
collections.description:
What does it mean to be human in a world where technology evolves faster than we do? Project Solara invites you to ponder this profound question through an extraordinary series of NFTs that tell the story of Solara—a being on the edge of transformation.

This collection begins with Solara as fully human: raw, beautiful, and connected to the world around her. As the series progresses, we witness her gradual evolution—glowing metallic enhancements replace flesh, and serene backdrops dissolve into the digital void. By the final piece, Solara stands as a near-complete AI, her humanity a distant memory, her existence both awe-inspiring and unsettling.

Project Solara isn’t just a collection; it’s a narrative about identity, progress, and the delicate balance between creation and loss. Each NFT is a chapter in Solara’s story—a visual exploration of how we reconcile the timeless beauty of humanity with the infinite potential of technology.
